 HN24[
] Monopsony power is market power on the buy (or input) side of the market. Weyerhaeuser, 549 U.S. at 320. "As such, a monopsony is to the buy side of the market what a monopoly is to the sell side[.]" Id. (citing Roger Blair & Jeffrey 
Harrison, Antitrust Policy and Monopsony, 76 Cornell L. Rev. 297, 301, 320 (1991)).

 The Court notes that the assertions for a finding of a monopoly made in Defendants' motion, Dkt. # 18, are indistinguishable 
from the assertions made to, and rejected by, the arbitrator during the arbitration, see Resp'ts' Arbitration Closing Br., Dkt. # 22, 
Ex. 18 at 67-104.

